summary:
I am a Team Player – I help others to grow, I am value delivery driven and able to deliver through others and deliver the expected results. I analyse and am able to simplify the complexity, open minded for the change and innovations. Having the strong visual memory I am good with numbers 
IT and ERP-systems.I lived and worked internationally with various teams in Russia, Uzbekistan, Kazahstan and Ukraine.

Work Experience:

- 8 years of experience in logistics and the transportation of petrochemicals 
- 6 years working in distribution and warehouse management
- 2 years of experience with the marketing and sales of polyethylene granules and propane gas in Eastern Europe, China and Central Asia
- For the last 2 years I have been participating in LEAN project ‘Redesign freezer pick zone’
- I led a number of successful implementations based on business cases with the Thermo Fisher Scientific, Bleiswijk, NL, such as:

1.	Shipment orders queue removal at conveyer belt- 500K USD saved annually 
2.	Manpower planning using ERP system data – removed the overtime hours, increased the quality of orders picking, increased planning efficiency.
3.	Optimization of boxes quantity in warehouse – sustained steadily the sufficient amount of boxes for packing team, accurate inventory, decreased the costs for firefighters’ risk insurance.
